    hadithEnglish:
      ' Narrated Ibn `Umar:\n\nAllahs Messenger (ﷺ) sent an army detachment and made Usama bin Zaid its commander. Some people criticized (spoke badly of) Usamas leadership. So Allahs Messenger (ﷺ) got up saying, If you people are criticizing Usamas leadership, you have already criticized the leadership of his father before. But Waaimullah (i.e., By Allah), he (i.e. Zaid) deserved the leadership, and he was one of the most beloved persons to me; and now this (his son Usama) is one of the dearest persons to me after him.',
