      ' Narrated `Umar bin Al-Khattab:\n\nDuring the lifetime of the Prophet (ﷺ) there was a man called `Abdullah whose nickname was Donkey, and he used to make Allahs Messenger (ﷺ) laugh. The Prophet (ﷺ) lashed him because of drinking (alcohol). And one-day he was brought to the Prophet (ﷺ) on the same charge and was lashed. On that, a man among the people said, O Allah, curse him ! How frequently he has been brought (to the Prophet (ﷺ) on such a charge)! The Prophet (ﷺ) said, Do not curse him, for by Allah, I know for he loves Allah and His Apostle.',
